Package org.gbif.api.vocabulary

Enum Habitat

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Habitat>
      • org.gbif.api.vocabulary.Habitat
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Habitat>
    public enum Habitat
extends Enum<Habitat>
    Very coarse habitat vocabulary matching the boolean biome flags found in the species profile extension. These also match the classifications provided by the WWF, BBC. http://www.ucmp.berkeley.edu/exhibits/biomes/index.php http://wwf.panda.org/about_our_earth/ecoregions/about/habitat_types/
    See Also:
    Species Profile Extension

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      FRESHWATER
      Freshwater habitats including rivers, lakes, ponds, wetlands, bogs, marsh, swamp and brackish waters!
      MARINE
      Marine habitats including the deep & open ocean, reefs and estuaries.
      TERRESTRIAL
      Terrestrial habitats cover all habitats on land including forests, deserts, grasslands, meadows, tundra, mangroves, farmland.
